      </p>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0636P0-01832'>
        <a name='S5LV0636P0_20020613_GCR_56'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-thomas-dixon' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S5LV0636P0_20020613_GCR_56' title='Link to this speech by Mr Thomas Dixon' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-thomas-dixon" title="Mr Thomas Dixon">Lord Glentoran</a></cite>
          <p class='first-para'>
            moved Amendment No. 112:
            <q>Page 13, leave out lines 11 to 22 and insert "take the oath of allegiance and the judicial oath or make the appropriate affirmation</q>
            The noble Lord said: Amendment No. 112 is grouped with Amendments Nos. 113 to 116, which. I do not believe it should be.
          </p>
