      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0636P0-01898'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0636P0_20020613_GCR_122' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        6.30 p.m.
      </p>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0636P0-01899'>
        <a name='S5LV0636P0_20020613_GCR_123'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-gareth-williams' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S5LV0636P0_20020613_GCR_123' title='Link to this speech by Mr Gareth Williams' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-gareth-williams" title="Mr Gareth Williams">Lord Williams of Mostyn</a></cite>
          <p class='first-para'>
            moved Amendment No. 126:
            <q>Page 17, line 37, at end insert&#x2014;</q>
            <q>( ) The Service is to be funded by the Secretary of State.</q>
            The noble and learned Lord said: This is a technical amendment. It makes it clear on the face of the Bill that the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland will be responsible for the funding of the prosecution service prior to devolution of justice functions. At the time of devolution, this provision will he amended to put the responsibility for funding on to the devolved administration.</p><p>
            Concerns were expressed in the House of Commons that the Bill was not clear enough. This amendment is to provide that clarity. I beg to move.</p><p>
            On Question, amendment agreed to.
          </p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
