            <q>Page 21, line 10, leave out "Authority" and insert "Board</q>
            The noble and learned Lord said: In moving Amendment No. 149, I shall speak also to Amendment No. 151. They are technical amendments, changing references to the <a href="/acts/police-northern-ireland-act-1998">Police (Northern Ireland) Act 1998</a>. When the Policing Board was established and the
            <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_100gc' title='Col. 100GC &mdash; HL Deb 13 June 2002 vol 636 c100GC' name='column_100gc' href='#column_100gc' rel='bookmark'>100GC</a>
